t he had used in his later work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aShakespeare 2022. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Shakespeare.2bisacsh  aCon-text.  aResource.  aShakespeare.  aSource.  acontext.  aintertextuality.  amemory.  aorality.  areading.  atheatre.1 aDrakakis, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615787440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526157874423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526157874/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles